WEBVTT

00:02.402 --> 00:05.338
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:05.405 --> 00:12.145
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:12.212 --> 00:14.447
<i>- ♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:14.514 --> 00:16.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:16.483 --> 00:18.017
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:18.084 --> 00:24.424
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:24.491 --> 00:26.426
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:26.493 --> 00:29.529
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:31.898 --> 00:33.299
- Hi, everyone.

00:33.366 --> 00:35.301
{\an1}Thanks for coming to another
Leaf Club meeting.

00:35.368 --> 00:37.137
This week's assignment
was to find a leaf

00:37.203 --> 00:40.373
you think is unique.
- Competition's over!

00:40.440 --> 00:41.841
Mine's the best!

00:41.908 --> 00:44.310
- How is that one the best?
[grunting]

00:44.377 --> 00:46.813
{\an3}See, look at this.
Do you have any idea

00:46.880 --> 00:48.415
{\an3}what I went through
to get this?

00:48.481 --> 00:49.716
- [spits]
- Ah!

00:49.783 --> 00:52.352
{\an1}- I don't respect you
or your leaf.

00:52.419 --> 00:53.987
- Y--you spat on me?

00:54.053 --> 00:55.388
Why, you little brat!

00:55.455 --> 00:58.458
[both struggle]
- Guys, guys.

00:58.525 --> 01:00.427
{\an1}This wasn't meant
to be a competition.

01:00.493 --> 01:02.362
{\an1}Everyone sees
leaves differently.

01:02.429 --> 01:04.931
Even our own two eyeballs
see the same leaf differently.

01:04.998 --> 01:07.700
See?
Right eye, left eye...

01:07.767 --> 01:09.436
Right eye, left eye.

01:09.502 --> 01:13.139
- [scoffs] Sounds weird.
- Try it.

01:13.206 --> 01:15.308
- Oh...
- Cool.

01:15.375 --> 01:18.411
{\an1}- That was really great
conflict resolution, Kathy.

01:18.478 --> 01:20.747
You should think about
giving advice professionally.

01:20.814 --> 01:22.816
Maybe you could add a
"life advice" section

01:22.882 --> 01:25.585
to your video vlogs.
- Well, I was gonna go home

01:25.652 --> 01:28.855
and put a puzzle together...
but helping others does sound

01:28.922 --> 01:30.457
{\an3}really nice.
You know, I'll do it.

01:30.523 --> 01:33.493
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

01:33.560 --> 01:36.563
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:36.629 --> 01:37.864
- Oh--hey, Kratz.

01:37.931 --> 01:40.200
- [giggling]

01:40.266 --> 01:41.935
- [sighs dreamily]

01:42.001 --> 01:44.938
<i>[upbeat synth music]</i>

01:45.004 --> 01:49.442
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:52.812 --> 01:54.280
<i>- Uh, hello, everyone.</i>

01:54.347 --> 01:56.015
<i>Today I'm starting</i>
<i>a new segment</i>

01:56.082 --> 01:58.084
<i>on my show,</i>
<i>"Leaf it to Kathy."</i>

01:58.151 --> 02:00.153
<i>[chuckles]</i>
<i>I enjoy a good leaf pun.</i>

02:00.220 --> 02:02.689
<i>Our first video question</i>
<i>is from Piri Piri.</i>

02:02.755 --> 02:05.291
<i>- Hey, Kathy.</i>
<i>My first question is:</i>

02:05.358 --> 02:07.227
<i>Do leaves ever feel sad</i>

02:07.293 --> 02:09.562
<i>when they're blown away</i>
<i>in the wind,</i>

02:09.628 --> 02:12.665
<i>leaving their dreams</i>
<i>to the whims of forces</i>

02:12.732 --> 02:15.335
<i>beyond their control?</i>

02:15.401 --> 02:17.237
{\an1}<i>- Hmm.</i>
<i>I think leaves just</i>

02:17.303 --> 02:19.572
<i>take life as it comes</i>
<i>and "leaf" themselves</i>

02:19.639 --> 02:21.274
<i>open to new experiences.</i>

02:21.341 --> 02:23.409
<i>Our next video question</i>
<i>is from Jeremy.</i>

02:23.476 --> 02:26.246
<i>- Hey, Kathy. Big fan.</i>
<i>So, I, uh,</i>

02:26.312 --> 02:28.114
<i>just got this plant</i>
<i>that I really like,</i>

02:28.181 --> 02:30.517
<i>but it's started to attract</i>
<i>all these bugs,</i>

02:30.583 --> 02:32.051
<i>and...</i>
<i>[screaming]</i>

02:32.118 --> 02:33.553
<i>Get away!</i>
<i>[screaming]</i>

02:33.620 --> 02:34.921
<i>- Oh, don't worry.</i>
<i>Those are just</i>

02:34.988 --> 02:36.022
<i>flesh-eating bugs.</i>

02:36.089 --> 02:37.323
<i>Your plant will be fine.</i>

02:37.390 --> 02:39.259
<i>Our last video is from Mikey.</i>

02:39.325 --> 02:41.327
<i>- Hey, Kathy.</i>
<i>My question is:</i>

02:41.394 --> 02:44.464
<i>as a fellow Internet star</i>
<i>and viral sensation,</i>

02:44.531 --> 02:46.266
<i>how do you deal</i>
<i>with the haters?</i>

02:46.332 --> 02:48.368
{\an1}<i>- Not really</i>
<i>a leaf-related question,</i>

02:48.434 --> 02:50.570
{\an1}<i>but I just tell them,</i>
<i>"Don't hate the player.</i>

02:50.637 --> 02:51.771
<i>Hate the game."</i>

02:51.838 --> 02:53.439
<i>[slurping]</i>

02:53.506 --> 02:55.241
<i>Well, that's it for today.</i>

02:55.308 --> 02:57.610
<i>Be sure to tune in</i>
<i>to the livestream later.</i>

02:57.677 --> 02:59.879
- Wow, Kathy's so great.

02:59.946 --> 03:02.048
{\an3}So, why'd you
call me over, Kratz?

03:02.115 --> 03:04.484
- Uh, yeah.
I was wondering,

03:04.551 --> 03:07.820
what exactly should I do
if I like someone

03:07.887 --> 03:10.356
who's really special and cool?

03:10.423 --> 03:12.325
- You like someone?
Who?

03:12.392 --> 03:15.328
- Well, they're really
smart and pretty.

03:15.395 --> 03:16.863
- [gasps]
Claire?

03:16.930 --> 03:18.898
- And robust.
And strong.

03:18.965 --> 03:21.267
- Rooter?
- And cool, and mature.

03:21.334 --> 03:22.802
- My mom?
- No,

03:22.869 --> 03:25.538
Miriam and I are just friends.
- Who, then?

03:25.605 --> 03:29.542
{\an3}- They're really good
at giving advice.

03:29.609 --> 03:31.778
- It's me?
- It's Kathy.

03:31.844 --> 03:34.614
I like Kathy.
- Oh...

03:34.681 --> 03:36.616
Oh!

03:36.683 --> 03:37.884
That's so cute.

03:37.951 --> 03:38.985
- Yeah.

03:39.052 --> 03:40.620
<i>[upbeat synth music]</i>

03:40.687 --> 03:42.755
<i>I've always thought</i>
<i>that she's amazing.</i>

03:42.822 --> 03:46.492
<i>One time, I saw her--</i>
<i>she had this leaf,</i>

03:46.559 --> 03:49.095
<i>and she was talking to it,</i>
<i>and holding it,</i>

03:49.162 --> 03:52.365
<i>and caressing it,</i>
<i>and I realized</i>

03:52.432 --> 03:55.602
<i>I wanted to be that leaf.</i>

03:55.668 --> 03:57.704
[smooching]

03:57.770 --> 03:58.705
[paper crumpling]

03:58.771 --> 04:00.440
[sighs]

04:00.506 --> 04:04.344
{\an3}- Kratz, you have to tell
Kathy how you feel!

04:04.410 --> 04:07.880
{\an1}- Are you crazy?
Kathy is way out of my league.

04:07.947 --> 04:09.582
- But you're so cool, Kratz.

04:09.649 --> 04:12.051
{\an3}You're an underground
comic book artist,

04:12.118 --> 04:14.287
the ace of subtext!
- [groans]

04:14.354 --> 04:15.588
[thud]
Harvey,

04:15.655 --> 04:17.557
{\an1}I wouldn't even know
where to start.

04:17.624 --> 04:19.225
{\an3}- Well, why don't you
ask her?

04:19.291 --> 04:22.028
{\an1}- I don't think you understand
how this works.

04:22.095 --> 04:26.065
- I mean, ask her
in a sneaky way.

04:26.132 --> 04:28.334
You ask Kathy
how to win her heart,

04:28.401 --> 04:31.104
but you say it's
for a friend.

04:31.170 --> 04:33.339
- Does that really work?
- Oh, yeah.

04:33.406 --> 04:35.274
{\an3}She won't suspect
a thing.

04:35.341 --> 04:38.044
{\an3}No one's ever
done that before.

04:38.111 --> 04:39.746
{\an1}- Huh.

04:39.812 --> 04:42.548
<i>[peaceful music]</i>

04:42.615 --> 04:44.851
- Hey, pretty lady.
- Hi, Harvey.

04:44.917 --> 04:47.020
{\an1}Just trying to get things
ready for my livestream

04:47.086 --> 04:49.055
later today.
- I've got a question

04:49.122 --> 04:52.659
{\an3}to submit to you:
are you single?

04:52.725 --> 04:55.028
- Oh, um, you're
a really sweet guy,

04:55.094 --> 04:57.730
but I think we should keep
our relationship professional.

04:57.797 --> 05:01.434
- You got the wrong idea.
I'm just asking because...

05:01.501 --> 05:03.503
{\an3}I wanted to know
if you had a type.

05:03.569 --> 05:06.539
You know, like, a type
of guy that you like--

05:06.606 --> 05:09.542
{\an3}like, would you be attracted
to someone like...

05:09.609 --> 05:13.246
{\an3}oh, say,
I don't know--Kratz?

05:13.312 --> 05:17.050
- Kratz, the tall, dreamy
underground comic artist?

05:17.116 --> 05:20.253
The ace of subtext?
[giggling nervously]

05:20.319 --> 05:23.423
{\an1}Um, I don't know.
I guess.

05:23.489 --> 05:27.660
{\an1}But... too bad he'd never
be interested in a girl like me.

05:27.727 --> 05:30.196
- [gasps, stammers]
[computer pings]

05:30.263 --> 05:32.165
{\an1}- Oh, speaking of
handsome devil now,

05:32.231 --> 05:33.833
{\an1}I have a video submission
from him.

05:33.900 --> 05:35.201
[computer beeps]

05:35.268 --> 05:36.736
<i>- [clears throat]</i>
<i>Uh...</i>

05:36.803 --> 05:40.573
<i>yeah, I have a question.</i>
<i>Uh...</i>

05:40.640 --> 05:42.875
{\an3}<i>- [whispering]</i>
<i>Friend! You have a friend.</i>

05:42.942 --> 05:45.645
<i>- Oh yeah.</i>
<i>So, I have a friend--</i>

05:45.712 --> 05:50.116
<i>a friend who isn't me--</i>
<i>and, uh...</i>

05:50.183 --> 05:51.417
<i>line?</i>

05:51.484 --> 05:53.619
<i>"What should my friend do</i>

05:53.686 --> 05:58.958
<i>to impress someone they like?</i>
<i>Romantically."</i>

05:59.025 --> 06:01.060
- [giggling]
Um, hi, Kratz.

06:01.127 --> 06:04.263
It was a really nice surprise
seeing your video in my inbox.

06:04.330 --> 06:07.433
[giggling]
Um, anyway, about your friend.

06:07.500 --> 06:09.435
Now, some say
a romantic gesture

06:09.502 --> 06:11.204
is the best way
to win someone's heart--

06:11.270 --> 06:13.439
like if somebody
got me glow leaves

06:13.506 --> 06:15.842
from the Deep Bark Cave,
that'd be cool.

06:15.908 --> 06:18.578
Um--but the best approach
for your friend

06:18.644 --> 06:22.381
is to be honest and open
about their feelings.

06:22.448 --> 06:25.718
{\an1}<i>It's super important just</i>
<i>to say how you feel.</i>

06:25.785 --> 06:27.553
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

06:27.620 --> 06:29.455
{\an3}- Okay!

06:29.522 --> 06:31.357
{\an3}- Kratz,
Kratz!

06:31.424 --> 06:33.126
{\an3}Did you see
Kathy's new video?

06:33.192 --> 06:35.628
- Yep, and I know
what I have to do.

06:35.695 --> 06:37.864
{\an3}- Great.
Good luck, buddy.

06:37.930 --> 06:41.801
I'm so glad he's finally
gonna tell her how he feels.

06:41.868 --> 06:43.069
<i>[peaceful music]</i>

06:43.136 --> 06:44.737
<i>- Uh, hey, everyone!</i>

06:44.804 --> 06:46.572
<i>Thanks for tuning in.</i>
<i>Today, I'll be answering</i>

06:46.639 --> 06:49.208
<i>your questions live.</i>
<i>And then, I don't know,</i>

06:49.275 --> 06:50.610
<i>maybe I'll end with</i>

06:50.676 --> 06:52.345
<i>a couple leaf reviews.</i>
<i>[laughs]</i>

06:52.411 --> 06:53.913
<i>Okay, so why don't we</i>
<i>get started?</i>

06:53.980 --> 06:56.249
<i>Our first video call</i>
<i>is from...</i>

06:56.315 --> 06:58.484
<i>Kratz!</i>
<i>Oh, uh--hi, Kratz.</i>

06:58.551 --> 07:01.420
<i>- Hi, Kathy.</i>
<i>I have a follow-up question</i>

07:01.487 --> 07:03.956
<i>regarding earlier.</i>
<i>Remember that cave</i>

07:04.023 --> 07:05.358
<i>you were talking about?</i>

07:05.424 --> 07:07.160
<i>How do I get out?</i>

07:07.226 --> 07:09.829
{\an1}- Wait, what?
Why are you in there?

07:09.896 --> 07:11.097
<i>- No reason.</i>

07:11.164 --> 07:12.965
{\an1}- Oh my gosh.
Okay, um, stay calm.

07:13.032 --> 07:16.669
{\an1}Uh, try--try heading
towards a light source.

07:16.736 --> 07:18.971
- Uh, okay.

07:19.038 --> 07:21.073
{\an8}<i>- What can you see?</i>
<i>Is it a way out?</i>

07:21.140 --> 07:23.776
- Uh...no.

07:23.843 --> 07:26.445
[monster roars]

07:26.512 --> 07:28.247
{\an1}- Kratz, what was that?
Are you okay?

07:28.314 --> 07:30.917
<i>- [shouting]</i>

07:30.983 --> 07:33.319
Cave monster!

07:33.386 --> 07:34.787
<i>- Okay, okay.</i>
<i>Um...</i>

07:34.854 --> 07:36.455
<i>try to get</i>
<i>to higher ground?</i>

07:36.522 --> 07:38.891
- [panting,
grunts]

07:38.958 --> 07:40.092
{\an3}[gasps]

07:40.860 --> 07:43.863
<i>- Did you get away?</i>
- I think so...

07:43.930 --> 07:45.798
[shouting]

07:45.865 --> 07:47.600
[bats squeaking]

07:47.667 --> 07:50.603
<i>- Okay, stay calm.</i>
<i>Just try calling for help.</i>

07:50.670 --> 07:51.938
[echoing]
- Help!

07:52.004 --> 07:54.006
[echoing, rumbling]

07:54.073 --> 07:55.208
[stone cracks]

07:55.274 --> 07:56.609
[shouting]

07:56.676 --> 07:59.178
<i>Ow, my nervous system.</i>

07:59.245 --> 08:00.813
{\an1}- Hang on, Kratz.
I'm coming to get you.

08:00.880 --> 08:02.815
<i>I'll be there soon,</i>
<i>just hold on.</i>

08:02.882 --> 08:04.684
- [panting]
It's real far.

08:04.750 --> 08:06.752
You must be a fast runner.
I've always been

08:06.819 --> 08:09.388
more of an indoor kid.
- Oh, I'm so bad

08:09.455 --> 08:11.090
when it comes to exercise.
[chuckles]

08:11.157 --> 08:13.626
But my advice has always been
to just enjoy a long walk

08:13.693 --> 08:16.495
every day.
- Wow, that's such good advice.

08:16.562 --> 08:19.699
Uh, so, how's
the livestream going?

08:19.765 --> 08:21.367
- It's going great, actually.

08:21.434 --> 08:23.302
I'm getting a ton of views
for some reason.

08:23.369 --> 08:26.138
{\an3}- Oh my gosh!
I'm so worried about Kratz--

08:26.205 --> 08:29.675
{\an3}but I wanna see where
all this chemistry is going.

08:29.742 --> 08:33.511
{\an1}- Oh, I guess Kathy likes Kratz.
I'm not jealous.

08:33.578 --> 08:35.581
- I'm almost there, Kratz.
Just keep moving.

08:35.648 --> 08:37.116
- I think I'll be okay.

08:37.183 --> 08:39.518
I've got a pretty good
sense of direction--

08:39.585 --> 08:41.654
[grunts, shouts]

08:41.721 --> 08:43.856
<i>- Kratz!</i>
<i>Are you okay?</i>

08:43.923 --> 08:46.292
- Uh...I think so?

08:46.359 --> 08:49.896
[monster growling]

08:49.962 --> 08:53.566
Yeah, Kathy, I don't think
I'm gonna make it.

08:53.633 --> 08:55.101
<i>- Kratz, no!</i>
<i>There's something</i>

08:55.167 --> 08:56.369
<i>more important</i>
<i>I have to tell you.</i>

08:56.435 --> 08:57.637
[phone beeps]

08:57.703 --> 09:00.106
- Well, I guess that's that.

09:00.172 --> 09:03.910
{\an3}Go ahead, monster.
I serve no greater purpose.

09:03.976 --> 09:07.113
[roaring]

09:07.179 --> 09:09.282
<i>[upbeat synth music]</i>

09:09.348 --> 09:11.050
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:11.117 --> 09:13.686
- Uh, hey, Kratz.

09:13.753 --> 09:16.555
{\an1}- Kathy?
Uh...how's it going?

09:16.622 --> 09:18.858
- It's great--um,
I mean, it's good.

09:18.925 --> 09:21.027
{\an3}Good. [laughs]
How are you?

09:21.093 --> 09:23.095
- Uh, I think I'm good.

09:23.162 --> 09:26.165
- Oh, Kratz.
- Kathy.

09:26.232 --> 09:27.233
- Kratz.

09:27.300 --> 09:29.168
[monster roars]

09:29.235 --> 09:30.903
You stay here.

09:30.970 --> 09:32.605
"Leaf" it to me.

09:32.672 --> 09:35.908
[monster roaring]

09:36.809 --> 09:38.210
[Kathy growling softly]

09:38.277 --> 09:39.879
[monster growling]

09:39.946 --> 09:41.614
- Uh...

09:41.681 --> 09:43.382
[monster growling]

09:43.449 --> 09:45.551
- Hey!
What's your problem?

09:45.618 --> 09:46.819
- [roaring]

09:46.886 --> 09:48.521
Huh?

09:48.587 --> 09:52.358
{\an1}...so, I don't know,
now it just feels weird.

09:52.425 --> 09:54.560
{\an1}I mean, I saw her
in the grocery store.

09:54.627 --> 09:56.896
{\an1}I said hi,
but she didn't say hi back.

09:56.963 --> 09:59.465
I thought we had this thing,
but now I don't know.

09:59.532 --> 10:01.734
What am I supposed to do?
- Well, honesty

10:01.801 --> 10:03.703
{\an3}is the most important part
of any relationship.

10:03.769 --> 10:05.371
{\an3}You need to tell her
how you feel.

10:05.438 --> 10:08.774
- Yeah, but what if she doesn't
feel the same way?

10:08.841 --> 10:11.544
- Well, some people are worth
taking that risk for.

10:11.610 --> 10:14.180
<i>[gentle music]</i>

10:14.246 --> 10:18.718
{\an1}- Huh...okay...cool, cool.
You know, you've really

10:18.784 --> 10:21.220
{\an1}given me a lot
to think about, here.

10:21.287 --> 10:22.722
- Hey.
- Hey.

10:22.788 --> 10:25.458
{\an3}- Uh, Kathy?
I--I--

10:25.524 --> 10:27.994
{\an1}- No, wait.
I have to tell you something.

10:28.060 --> 10:29.795
I have to be honest
about how I feel.

10:29.862 --> 10:32.465
[inhales deeply]
Kratz, I--

10:32.531 --> 10:35.668
{\an3}- I like you!
I--I like you a lot.

10:35.735 --> 10:37.703
- Glow leaves?

10:37.770 --> 10:40.072
{\an3}- You take my breath away,
Kathy.

10:40.139 --> 10:42.742
{\an3}Although that could be
a collapsed lung.

10:42.808 --> 10:45.177
Anyway, you wanna
hang out sometime?

10:45.244 --> 10:47.213
{\an1}- Yeah.
I'd like that.

10:47.279 --> 10:50.216
<i>[cheery music]</i>

10:50.282 --> 10:52.451
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:52.518 --> 10:54.620
- [sighs contentedly]

10:54.687 --> 10:57.723
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:58.157 --> 11:00.226
<i>- Oh, gosh.</i>
<i>I almost forgot my laptop.</i>

11:00.292 --> 11:01.794
My mom would've been so mad.

11:01.861 --> 11:03.496
<i>Hey, everyone.</i>
<i>Thanks for tuning into</i>

11:03.562 --> 11:05.297
<i>the stream.</i>
<i>Today, Kratz and I</i>

11:05.364 --> 11:07.133
<i>helped resolve</i>
<i>each other's problems,</i>

11:07.199 --> 11:09.502
<i>so, uh...</i>
<i>- You could say we feel pretty</i>

11:09.568 --> 11:11.537
<i>re-"leaf"-ed.</i>
<i>- Kratz,</i>

11:11.604 --> 11:13.773
<i>was that a leaf pun?</i>
<i>[both laugh]</i>

11:13.839 --> 11:15.274
<i>[beeping]</i>
<i>Oh, my battery.</i>

11:16.776 --> 11:19.545
[grunting]

11:19.612 --> 11:22.548
[all heaving and panting]

11:22.615 --> 11:24.650
{\an3}- All right, fellas.
All aboard.

11:24.717 --> 11:26.218
Come on, come on.

11:26.285 --> 11:28.220
[both grunting]

11:28.287 --> 11:30.856
{\an1}- Thanks again for organizing
this cabin retreat, Rooter.

11:30.923 --> 11:33.392
{\an3}- Harvey, how many times
do I have to tell you?

11:33.459 --> 11:38.097
This is not a cabin retreat.
This is a wilderness trial.

11:38.164 --> 11:39.265
- [struggling]

11:39.331 --> 11:40.433
[grunts,
thuds]

11:40.499 --> 11:42.001
- I worry about you guys,

11:42.068 --> 11:44.837
so I'm gonna teach you
some survival skills.

11:44.904 --> 11:47.406
{\an3}That way, when
the apocalypse comes,

11:47.473 --> 11:49.742
{\an3}you'll be strong,
capable men--

11:49.809 --> 11:51.710
not soft little
wiener babies.

11:51.777 --> 11:54.213
{\an1}- I am not a wiener baby--
[shouts]

11:54.280 --> 11:56.449
{\an1}[sobs]
I just bit my tongue.

11:56.515 --> 11:59.285
{\an3}- All right, before we start,
I'm gonna give you guys

11:59.351 --> 12:02.054
{\an3}something my dad gave me
when I was just a lad.

12:02.121 --> 12:05.091
{\an3}Take a gander at this!
"Don't Die:

12:05.157 --> 12:09.495
{\an3}A Child's Guide to Survival
by Dr. Myles Idyllwild."

12:09.562 --> 12:12.832
This is the essential guide
to surviving in the wild--

12:12.898 --> 12:15.301
on your own!
Any questions?

12:15.367 --> 12:19.004
{\an3}- Where's the boat seatbelts?
I can't seem to find mine.

12:19.071 --> 12:21.607
- Yeah, and where can I
plug in my humidifier?

12:21.674 --> 12:23.776
I feel a nasty nosebleed comin'.

12:23.843 --> 12:25.411
{\an3}- Anyone want
some artichoke dip?

12:25.478 --> 12:27.046
It's vegan.
- Oh, yeah.

12:27.113 --> 12:28.314
I love artichoke dip.
- Ooh, ooh, me!

12:28.380 --> 12:29.715
- Ooh, yeah.

12:29.782 --> 12:31.417
- That sounds wonderful.
- Count me in.

12:31.484 --> 12:34.420
<i>[drum music]</i>

12:34.487 --> 12:41.427
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:41.494 --> 12:45.364
[group screaming]

12:45.431 --> 12:46.966
{\an3}- Man, what's
with this water?

12:47.032 --> 12:49.602
{\an3}This is nothin' like
the water in my bathtub.

12:49.668 --> 12:51.971
- Time to get acquainted
with your surroundings.

12:52.037 --> 12:56.108
Now, what do you see?
- All I see is a fork.

12:56.175 --> 12:58.878
{\an1}Ah, but it's dirty.
How am I supposed to eat

12:58.944 --> 13:00.946
my pasta salad?
- Now, tell me:

13:01.013 --> 13:02.715
what does chapter one say?

13:02.781 --> 13:06.685
{\an1}- It says...
"expect the unexpected"?

13:06.752 --> 13:09.388
- That's right.
[machinery clanking]

13:09.455 --> 13:11.991
- Wait, what?
- The only way you'll learn

13:12.057 --> 13:14.927
to fend for yourselves
is if I leave you.

13:14.994 --> 13:17.129
This is for your own good.

13:17.196 --> 13:19.732
{\an3}[shouting]
Follow the guidebook!

13:19.798 --> 13:21.467
[all shouting]

13:21.534 --> 13:23.269
- Okay, okay--
nobody panic.

13:23.335 --> 13:25.504
Let's just try to come up
with a plan.

13:25.571 --> 13:27.506
{\an1}- Hey, maybe if we
think positive

13:27.573 --> 13:29.408
{\an1}and believe in ourselves,
we can--

13:29.475 --> 13:32.411
[all screaming]

13:32.478 --> 13:33.445
[water splashing]

13:33.512 --> 13:36.248
[all groaning]

13:36.315 --> 13:40.085
{\an1}- [sighs] Well, I guess I
should've read chapter two:

13:40.152 --> 13:42.354
"Don't go chasing
waterfalls."

13:42.421 --> 13:45.958
{\an1}Guys, maybe Rooter's right.
Maybe we are too soft

13:46.025 --> 13:48.360
{\an1}for this crazy world.
From now on,

13:48.427 --> 13:51.163
we need to read this book
before we do anything.

13:51.230 --> 13:52.965
- But we're in
the middle of nowhere,

13:53.032 --> 13:55.768
with no way to get home.
What's your smart book say

13:55.834 --> 13:57.770
about that?
- Well,

13:57.836 --> 14:00.639
chapter three says,
"Build a shelter."

14:00.706 --> 14:02.608
<i>[up-tempo music]</i>

14:02.675 --> 14:03.842
[finger tapping]

14:03.909 --> 14:05.644
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:05.711 --> 14:07.246
- [panicked shouting]

14:07.313 --> 14:10.749
- It's dark! Help!
[screaming]

14:10.816 --> 14:13.586
[panting]

14:13.652 --> 14:15.020
[stake clatters]
- Ow.

14:15.087 --> 14:16.989
- Well, it took
a lot of work,

14:17.056 --> 14:18.891
{\an1}but I think our tent
turned out great.

14:18.958 --> 14:21.126
{\an1}- It's like
a fine hotel, yo.

14:21.193 --> 14:23.162
- Now, what to do for food?

14:23.229 --> 14:27.466
Chapter four: "foraging and
collecting nature's bounty."

14:27.533 --> 14:30.336
- Hey, Harvey, what about
these berries over here?

14:30.402 --> 14:33.472
- Uh, the book says to test
before eating.

14:33.539 --> 14:35.908
{\an1}- Okay.
Hey, Kratz, come here.

14:35.975 --> 14:37.943
- Okay.
- Just gonna make sure

14:38.010 --> 14:40.346
this is safe.
[berry rustling]

14:40.412 --> 14:43.349
{\an1}- Yep, there's definitely
some poison in there.

14:43.415 --> 14:46.885
{\an1}- It also says red berries
in this region are safe to eat.

14:46.952 --> 14:49.021
Oh, did you know that
already, Technobear?

14:49.088 --> 14:51.624
{\an3}[munching]
Know what?

14:51.690 --> 14:54.393
- Okay.
It took us five hours,

14:54.460 --> 14:55.761
but we built a fire.

14:55.828 --> 14:58.163
Man, this book really is
a lifesaver.

14:58.230 --> 15:01.033
{\an3}- Hey, Harvey, let me
take a turn reading the book.

15:01.100 --> 15:03.002
{\an1}- Sure, Dade.
How about I throw the book

15:03.068 --> 15:04.937
over to you?
- Yeah, throw it over to me

15:05.004 --> 15:06.472
{\an3}and I'll catch it
with my hands.

15:06.538 --> 15:09.475
- Roger that--
throwin' the book to your hands.

15:09.541 --> 15:10.542
[smack]
- [grunts]

15:10.609 --> 15:12.711
[book sizzles]

15:12.778 --> 15:14.313
{\an3}[screaming]

15:14.380 --> 15:15.981
[all screaming]

15:16.048 --> 15:18.917
- [screaming and grunting]

15:18.984 --> 15:20.519
- Uh, do something!

15:20.586 --> 15:23.022
[all shouting in panic]

15:23.088 --> 15:25.524
- Oh, no, no, no, no, no!

15:25.591 --> 15:29.128
The pages are all messed up.
I hate to say this, but...

15:29.194 --> 15:31.597
I think we're on our own now.
- What?

15:31.664 --> 15:34.566
{\an1}- You said we wouldn't be able
to survive on our own.

15:34.633 --> 15:36.168
- I remember!
He said that.

15:36.235 --> 15:38.437
You said that!
- Yeah, but

15:38.504 --> 15:40.939
the book's totally ruined.
- Well... [stammers]

15:41.006 --> 15:42.875
{\an1}Maybe you're just
readin' it wrong, buddy.

15:42.941 --> 15:45.511
I'm just gonna look up
how to treat my hangnail.

15:45.577 --> 15:47.079
Ah, let's see, here...

15:47.146 --> 15:50.749
"Cover face with--
with honey."

15:50.816 --> 15:52.751
[panting and grunting]

15:52.818 --> 15:54.219
[bees buzzing]

15:54.286 --> 15:56.622
[screams]
Oh, gosh, it stings!

15:56.689 --> 15:58.757
[shouts]
But I don't even notice

15:58.824 --> 16:02.061
my finger now, so, see?
The guide's still helping us.

16:02.127 --> 16:04.229
{\an3}- Yo, Dade.
What's that book say

16:04.296 --> 16:06.465
about punk snakes
who won't let go of your arm?

16:06.532 --> 16:08.967
Hmm, that's either
some sort of vase,

16:09.034 --> 16:11.403
or two faces kissin'...

16:11.470 --> 16:13.672
All right, snake,
I'm about to kiss you up.

16:13.739 --> 16:15.874
[smooching,
snake hissing]

16:15.941 --> 16:18.210
{\an1}- That's right, TB,
you smooch that thing.

16:18.277 --> 16:20.412
- Okay, that makes zero sense.
[coins clattering]

16:20.479 --> 16:23.415
{\an9}- Guys, I just dropped
a bunch of pennies.

16:23.482 --> 16:25.250
- Well, check the guide!
- The guide, the guide!

16:25.317 --> 16:26.719
{\an3}- Check it--check the guide.
Check it.

16:26.785 --> 16:28.253
- All the back pages

16:28.320 --> 16:30.989
are just a bunch of horses
laughing at me.

16:31.056 --> 16:33.292
Wow, this really helps
put everything

16:33.359 --> 16:36.328
in a new perspective.
- It sure does, bro.

16:36.395 --> 16:39.431
- Okay, then...
I'm just gonna go up

16:39.498 --> 16:42.201
on this hillside and see
if I can find a way home.

16:42.267 --> 16:46.572
{\an1}- We have the guidebook.
Don't worry, we'll be fine.

16:46.638 --> 16:50.275
- Okay, maybe I can see
Littlebark from way up here.

16:50.342 --> 16:52.778
Okay, not the scary volcano...

16:52.845 --> 16:54.980
Oh, hey--Ira Fingerman.

16:55.047 --> 16:57.649
There's Mustache Mountain,
and...

16:57.716 --> 16:59.551
hey!
There's my house.

16:59.618 --> 17:03.021
If we take off now,
we'll be home in no time.

17:03.088 --> 17:05.124
Guys!
I don't think we're too far

17:05.190 --> 17:08.093
from civil...ization?

17:08.160 --> 17:10.194
[flames crackling]

17:10.262 --> 17:13.365
[mud bubbling]
- [mumbles incoherently]

17:13.432 --> 17:15.067
- [grunting]

17:15.134 --> 17:17.136
- Harvey!
Oh, you're alive!

17:17.202 --> 17:19.637
{\an1}- I was gone
for only five minutes.

17:19.704 --> 17:23.541
{\an3}- Oh, sweet, sweet child.
We endured so many dangers:

17:23.608 --> 17:27.546
the plague, the uprising,
the second uprising.

17:27.613 --> 17:29.348
- The only reason
we're still alive

17:29.415 --> 17:31.016
{\an3}is the guide told us
what to do.

17:31.083 --> 17:32.451
<i>[apprehensive music]</i>

17:32.518 --> 17:34.720
{\an3}- What do we do next,
guide?

17:34.787 --> 17:36.588
- Guys, forget the guidebook.

17:36.655 --> 17:38.590
You're all just
hurting yourselves.

17:38.657 --> 17:40.659
Now, let's go.

17:40.726 --> 17:41.894
Guys?

17:41.960 --> 17:43.929
{\an1}Why are you just
staring at me?

17:43.996 --> 17:46.265
- What do you mean,
"forget the guide"?

17:46.331 --> 17:49.535
- The guide is the only thing
protecting us.

17:49.601 --> 17:52.204
- Buddy, I love you,
but you sound insane.

17:52.271 --> 17:53.806
- Wait, what?
What?

17:53.872 --> 17:55.274
<i>[percussive chanting music]</i>

17:55.340 --> 17:56.175
[screams]

17:56.241 --> 17:57.643
[crickets chirping]

17:57.709 --> 18:00.746
[snoring]

18:01.547 --> 18:04.683
- The guide was so helpful,
but now...

18:04.750 --> 18:07.219
now it looks like a wet pizza.

18:07.286 --> 18:09.288
They're taking it so literally.

18:09.354 --> 18:11.824
Only if it would say something
that would...

18:11.890 --> 18:14.960
snap them
out of it.

18:15.027 --> 18:17.896
<i>[sneaky music]</i>

18:17.963 --> 18:19.431
Bleh!

18:19.498 --> 18:21.700
{\an1}- Follow whatever
the guide says, bro.

18:21.767 --> 18:26.104
[all snoring]
- I'm talking in my sleep.

18:26.171 --> 18:27.706
[mud squelches]

18:27.773 --> 18:30.042
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:30.108 --> 18:31.143
[mud squelching]

18:31.210 --> 18:33.011
[group snoring]

18:33.078 --> 18:35.013
{\an3}- Protect...
[snores]

18:35.080 --> 18:36.849
{\an3}the...
guidebook!

18:36.915 --> 18:38.851
[panicked shouting]

18:38.917 --> 18:41.487
Okay, it's safe.
- Morning, guys.

18:41.553 --> 18:46.458
What's going on?
I just woke up--in the cage.

18:46.525 --> 18:48.293
How about we check in
with the guide?

18:48.360 --> 18:50.295
Maybe it says
something important.

18:50.362 --> 18:52.364
- Hey, there's
a new chapter.

18:52.431 --> 18:55.200
- "Chapter nine:
stop reading me"?

18:55.267 --> 18:57.703
"This guide has taught you
all it can.

18:57.769 --> 19:01.306
"It's time to put your skills
to use and find a way home.

19:01.373 --> 19:03.942
"Also, stop acting like
crazy people

19:04.009 --> 19:05.711
"and put Band-Aids
on those scabs,

19:05.777 --> 19:07.145
"because they look infected.

19:07.212 --> 19:09.648
"The end of book.
No more.

19:09.715 --> 19:10.883
"Stop, I mean it.

19:10.949 --> 19:12.351
"Bye, I love you"?

19:12.417 --> 19:15.487
{\an1}- Wait, that's it?
We're just supposed to...

19:15.554 --> 19:16.688
{\an1}move on?

19:16.755 --> 19:18.223
<i>[tense string music]</i>

19:18.290 --> 19:21.660
- Guys, you heard
what the guidebook said.

19:21.727 --> 19:22.961
{\an3}[grunts]

19:23.028 --> 19:25.564
[swooshing]

19:25.631 --> 19:28.567
<i>[hopeful music]</i>

19:28.634 --> 19:31.403
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:31.470 --> 19:32.571
[thud]

19:32.638 --> 19:34.573
Ah, well--you know.
You get the gesture.

19:34.640 --> 19:37.843
- That was beautiful, guys.
Can you let me outta here now?

19:37.910 --> 19:40.612
- Oh, of course, buddy.
- What are we gonna do now?

19:40.679 --> 19:41.780
- Probably die.

19:41.847 --> 19:43.515
{\an3}- No!
Being out here

19:43.582 --> 19:45.584
has taught us something
about ourselves.

19:45.651 --> 19:48.053
We like air conditioning
and pillows.

19:48.120 --> 19:50.589
{\an1}- And sometimes
baking butter tarts.

19:50.656 --> 19:53.258
- The world may be dangerous,
but we can survive it

19:53.325 --> 19:56.762
just the way we are--
as soft boys.

19:56.828 --> 19:58.564
[together]
Yeah!

19:58.630 --> 20:00.766
- All right,
first thing we need to do

20:00.832 --> 20:03.168
is find
a clear direction towards home.

20:03.235 --> 20:04.870
- Hey, hey--
hey, wait a second.

20:04.937 --> 20:07.472
[sniffs]
Pumpkin spice vanilla!

20:07.539 --> 20:09.207
That's from
the scented candle store

20:09.274 --> 20:10.342
next to my house.

20:10.409 --> 20:12.678
[sniffing]
That way!

20:12.744 --> 20:15.681
[all panting]

20:15.747 --> 20:17.649
{\an3}- Oh, no.

20:17.716 --> 20:19.184
[monster roars]

20:19.251 --> 20:22.688
- Someone do something!
- Uh, sir?

20:22.754 --> 20:25.791
If you let us go by, I'll...
give you one of

20:25.857 --> 20:29.695
my 20% coupons to "Pillows,
Sinks, &amp; Further."

20:29.761 --> 20:32.264
- [growls approvingly]

20:32.331 --> 20:35.334
<i>[up-tempo music]</i>

20:35.400 --> 20:36.768
- ♪ I'm a little teapot ♪

20:36.835 --> 20:38.203
[together]
♪ Short and stout ♪

20:38.270 --> 20:39.738
- ♪ Here is my handle ♪

20:39.805 --> 20:41.740
[together]
♪ Here is my spout ♪

20:41.807 --> 20:44.509
- ♪ When I get all steamed up,
hear me shout ♪

20:44.576 --> 20:47.112
♪ Tip me over
and pour me out ♪

20:47.179 --> 20:49.581
Oh, no!
There's mud blocking our path.

20:49.648 --> 20:52.250
- Yo, yo, yo.
We need some of those

20:52.317 --> 20:54.653
super legit cleats
they use for climbing mountains.

20:54.720 --> 20:56.188
Where are we gonna
get 'em, though?

20:56.254 --> 20:58.090
{\an1}- Oh, well, I don't know
about cleats,

20:58.156 --> 21:00.258
but I happen to have
the entire wardrobe

21:00.325 --> 21:03.395
{\an1}from last year's
Littlebark Dance Extravaganza.

21:03.462 --> 21:05.764
Gentlemen, how do
we feel about...

21:05.831 --> 21:07.332
heels?

21:07.399 --> 21:09.334
[together]
Ooh.

21:09.401 --> 21:11.103
- ♪ Left, left ♪

21:11.169 --> 21:13.071
♪ Left, height, left ♪

21:13.138 --> 21:14.906
[together]
♪ Left, left ♪

21:14.973 --> 21:17.342
♪ Left, height, left ♪

21:17.409 --> 21:20.879
{\an3}- Boys, it's no easy feat
to survive in the wild.

21:20.946 --> 21:22.347
You gave it your all.

21:22.414 --> 21:24.783
Harvey,
you didn't make it,

21:24.850 --> 21:27.552
but you spent your last moments
in the woods,

21:27.619 --> 21:29.021
like men.

21:29.087 --> 21:32.491
Dade, Technobear, et cetera.

21:32.557 --> 21:34.459
You were like brothers to me--

21:34.526 --> 21:38.864
weak, wiener-baby brothers.
And I know, if you were here

21:38.930 --> 21:41.500
right now, you'd say--
- Stop the funeral!

21:41.566 --> 21:43.402
The soft boys
have returned.

21:43.468 --> 21:45.837
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

21:45.904 --> 21:47.773
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:47.839 --> 21:51.043
- You guys survived!
- And we did half of it

21:51.109 --> 21:54.012
by ourselves.
- I'm so proud!

21:54.079 --> 21:56.314
{\an1}You boys are tougher
than I thought.

21:56.381 --> 21:58.684
[thudding,
groaning]

21:58.750 --> 22:00.452
- Ow, owwie...

22:02.387 --> 22:05.390
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

22:05.457 --> 22:12.698
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:17.135 --> 22:24.376
<i>♪ ♪</i>
